Name: Label
Description: A display label for the number range. Supports multiple language versions of the same content as well as optional formatting of the content. Repeat for labels with different content, for example, labels with differing length limitations.

Name: Low
Description: The lower bound of the range expressed in the data type xs:decimal. If not present, then there is no lower bound.

Name: LowDouble
Description: The lower bound of the range expressed in the data type xs:double. If not present, then there is no lower bound.

Name: High
Description: The upper bound of the range in the data type xs:decimal. If not present, then there is no upper bound.

Name: HighDouble
Description: The upper bound of the range in the data type xs:double. If not present, then there is no upper bound.

Name: TopCode
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or greater than this value has been coded as the top-code value. Expressed in the data type xs:decimal.

Name: TopCodeDouble
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or greater than this value has been coded as the top-code value. Expressed in the data type xs:decimal.

Name: BottomCode
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or less than this value has been coded as the bottom-code value. Expressed in the data type xs:double.

Name: BottomCodeDouble
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or less than this value has been coded as the bottom-code value. Expressed in the data type xs:double.

Name: RegExp
Description: Regular expression defining the allowed syntax of the number.
